.TH "hrtimer_init" 9 "hrtimer_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hrtimer_init \- initialize a timer to the given clock
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" hrtimer_init
.BI "(struct hrtimer *timer "  ","
.BI "clockid_t clock_id "  ","
.BI "enum hrtimer_mode mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "timer" 12
the timer to be initialized
.IP "clock_id" 12
the clock to be used
.IP "mode" 12
The modes which are relevant for intitialization:
HRTIMER_MODE_ABS, HRTIMER_MODE_REL, HRTIMER_MODE_ABS_SOFT,
HRTIMER_MODE_REL_SOFT

The PINNED variants of the above can be handed in,
but the PINNED bit is ignored as pinning happens
when the hrtimer is started
